Moloto Mothapo started working for the ANC Parliamentary caucus in 2005 and has served under 7 ANC chief whips over the past 12 years. PARLIAMENT - The African National Congress (ANC)'s spokesperson in Parliament Moloto Mothapo has resigned.Mothapo started working for the ANC Parliamentary caucus in 2005 and has served under seven different ANC chief whips over the past 12 years.He's resignation takes effect on 14 February.#ANCCaucus spokesperson Moloto Mothapo has resigned GDANC chief whip Jackson Mthembu says Mothapo served with &quot;dedication, diligence and uncompromising loyalty&quot; and has wished him well in his future endeavours.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)